94
00:04:48,302 --> 00:04:52,765
That can be summarized pretty easily with the age-old six question words,

95
00:04:52,805 --> 00:04:55,066
your why, who, where, what, when, and how.

96
00:04:56,126 --> 00:04:58,708
So I'm going to break these down into what they mean for the story,

97
00:04:58,728 --> 00:05:01,109
and then we're going to break them down into what they mean for gameplay.

98
00:05:01,829 --> 00:05:01,969
So...

99
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:06,692
From a story perspective, our Y here represents our theme.

100
00:05:06,793 --> 00:05:09,855
And this is the purpose of the thing that you're making.

101
00:05:09,935 --> 00:05:12,577
It's the message you're trying to get to the viewer, player,

102
00:05:13,258 --> 00:05:16,140
experiencer, whatever they're calling VR now, et cetera.

103
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:19,182
Your who is your characters.

104
00:05:19,382 --> 00:05:20,603
And often, your characters are going

105
00:05:20,623 --> 00:05:22,164
to embody some part of your theme.

106
00:05:22,204 --> 00:05:24,866
They're the vessels by which you're telling the story.

107
00:05:26,528 --> 00:05:28,569
There's the setting, so when and where it's happening.

108
00:05:30,311 --> 00:05:32,092
The what, which is your plot and events.

109
00:05:32,192 --> 00:05:34,213
So this is when we start getting down

110
00:05:34,253 --> 00:05:36,654
into the beat by beat progression

111
00:05:36,874 --> 00:05:38,175
of the actual story you're telling.

112
00:05:39,716 --> 00:05:43,018
When is the time of events relative to each other?

113
00:05:43,218 --> 00:05:45,860
So it's how those things from our plot and events

114
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:48,381
are what are structured and paced next to each other.

115
00:05:49,922 --> 00:05:51,363
And then how is our presentation?

116
00:05:51,683 --> 00:05:53,805
So how are you telling the story?

117
00:05:54,305 --> 00:05:59,108
How are you showing these characters, these settings, these plots, these time of events

118
00:05:59,968 --> 00:06:01,409
to support your theme?

119
00:06:01,529 --> 00:06:02,350
So it kind of is...

120
00:06:02,530 --> 00:06:03,911
It's not really a linear list.

121
00:06:03,971 --> 00:06:07,433
It's really a cyclical list, always going back to that theme and that feeling.

122
00:06:08,774 --> 00:06:09,755
That might be really confusing.

123
00:06:10,595 --> 00:06:15,318
So I'm going to go into an example using a movie you might have guessed that I like a

